["Compaction tuning for when context nears token limits, including history share, reserve headroom, and pre-compaction memory flush behavior. Use when long-running sessions need stable continuity under tight context windows.","用于在上下文接近令牌上限时调整压缩行为，包括历史占比、保留空间和压缩前记忆刷写。适合需要在紧张上下文窗口下保持稳定连续性的长会话。"],
["压缩 tuning for when context nears token limits, including history share, reserve headroom, and pre-compaction memory flush behavior. Use this when long-running sessions need stable continuity under tight context windows.","用于在上下文接近令牌上限时调整压缩行为，包括历史占比、保留空间和压缩前记忆刷写。适合需要在紧张上下文窗口下保持稳定连续性的长会话。"],
["Compaction Identifier Instructions","压缩标识符说明"],
["Custom identifier-preservation instruction text used when identifierPolicy=\"custom\". Keep this explicit and safety-focused so compaction summaries do not rewrite opaque IDs, URLs, hosts, or ports.","当 identifierPolicy=\"custom\" 时使用的自定义标识符保留说明文本。请保持其明确且以安全为导向，避免压缩摘要改写不透明 ID、URL、主机或端口。"],
["Compaction Identifier Policy","压缩标识符策略"],
["Identifier-preservation policy for compaction summaries: \"strict\" prepends built-in opaque-identifier retention guidance (default), \"off\" disables this prefix, and \"custom\" uses identifierInstructions. Keep \"strict\" unless you have a specific compatibility need.","压缩摘要的标识符保留策略：“strict” 会在前面附加内置的不透明标识符保留指引（默认），“off” 禁用此前缀，“custom” 使用 identifierInstructions。除非有明确兼容性需求，否则建议保持 “strict”。"],
["Compaction Keep Recent Tokens","压缩保留最近令牌数"],
["Minimum token budget preserved from the most recent conversation window during compaction. Use higher values to protect immediate context continuity and lower values to keep more long-tail history.","压缩期间从最近对话窗口中保留的最小令牌预算。更高的值可保护最近上下文连续性，更低的值则能保留更多长尾历史。"],
["Compaction Max History Share","压缩最大历史占比"],
["Max fraction of total context budget allowed for retained history after compaction (range 0.1-0.9). Use lower shares for more generation headroom or higher shares for deeper historical continuity.","压缩后允许保留历史占总上下文预算的最大比例（范围 0.1-0.9）。较低占比可留出更多生成空间，较高占比则可保留更深的历史连续性。"],
["Compaction Memory Flush","压缩前记忆刷写"],
["Pre-compaction memory flush settings that run an agentic memory write before heavy compaction. Keep enabled for long sessions so salient context is persisted before aggressive trimming.","重压缩前执行的记忆刷写设置，会在大幅压缩前先进行一次代理式记忆写入。长会话建议保持启用，以便在激进裁剪前保存关键信息。"],
["Compaction Memory Flush Enabled","启用压缩前记忆刷写"],
["Enable pre-compaction memory flush before the runtime performs stronger history reduction near token limits. Keep enabled unless you intentionally disable memory side effects in constrained environments.","在运行时接近令牌上限并执行更强历史压缩前，先启用记忆刷写。除非你明确要在受限环境中禁用记忆副作用，否则建议保持开启。"],
["Compaction Memory Flush Transcript Size Threshold","压缩前记忆刷写转录大小阈值"],
["Forces pre-compaction memory flush when transcript file size reaches this threshold (bytes or strings like \"2mb\"). Use to prevent long-session hangs even when token counters are stale; set to 0 to disable.","当转录文件大小达到该阈值时，强制执行压缩前记忆刷写（字节或如 “2mb” 的字符串）。可用于在令牌计数器失准时防止长会话卡住；设为 0 可禁用。"],
["Compaction Memory Flush Prompt","压缩前记忆刷写提示"],
["User-prompt template used for the pre-compaction memory flush turn when generating memory candidates. Use only when you need custom extraction instructions beyond the default memory flush behavior.","在压缩前记忆刷写回合生成记忆候选时使用的用户提示模板。仅当你需要超出默认记忆刷写行为的自定义提取说明时才使用。"],
["Compaction Memory Flush Soft Threshold","压缩前记忆刷写软阈值"],
["Threshold distance to compaction (in tokens) that triggers pre-compaction memory flush execution. Use earlier thresholds for safer persistence, or tighter thresholds for lower flush frequency.","距离触发压缩的阈值（以令牌计）达到该范围时，会执行压缩前记忆刷写。较早阈值更安全，较紧阈值则可减少刷写频率。"],
["Compaction Memory Flush System Prompt","压缩前记忆刷写系统提示"],
["System-prompt override for the pre-compaction memory flush turn to control extraction style and safety constraints. Use carefully so custom instructions do not reduce memory quality or leak sensitive context.","用于压缩前记忆刷写回合的系统提示覆盖项，可控制提取风格和安全约束。请谨慎使用，避免自定义说明降低记忆质量或泄露敏感上下文。"],
["Compaction Strategy Mode","压缩策略模式"],
["Compaction strategy mode: \"default\" uses baseline behavior, while \"safeguard\" applies stricter guardrails to preserve recent context. Keep \"default\" unless you observe aggressive history loss near limit boundaries.","压缩策略模式：“default” 使用基线行为，“safeguard” 会应用更严格的保护措施以保留最近上下文。除非你观察到临界边界附近出现激进的历史丢失，否则建议保持 “default”。"],
["Agent-to-Agent Tool Access","代理到代理工具访问"],
["Policy for allowing agent-to-agent tool calls and constraining which target agents can be reached. Keep disabled or tightly scoped unless cross-agent orchestration is intentionally enabled.","用于控制代理之间工具调用是否允许，以及可达目标代理范围的策略。除非你明确启用了跨代理编排，否则建议保持禁用或严格收窄。"],
["Agent-to-Agent Target Allowlist","代理到代理目标允许列表"],
["Allowlist of target agent IDs permitted for agent_to_agent calls when orchestration is enabled. Use explicit allowlists to avoid uncontrolled cross-agent call graphs.","当启用编排时，允许 agent_to_agent 调用访问的目标代理 ID 白名单。建议使用显式白名单，避免出现不可控的跨代理调用图。"],
["Enable Agent-to-Agent Tool","启用代理到代理工具"],
["Enables the agent_to_agent tool surface so one agent can invoke another agent at runtime. Keep off in simple deployments and enable only when orchestration value outweighs complexity.","启用 agent_to_agent 工具能力，让一个代理可以在运行时调用另一个代理。简单部署中建议关闭，只有在编排收益明显高于复杂度时再启用。"],
["Tool Allowlist","工具允许列表"],
["Absolute tool allowlist that replaces profile-derived defaults for strict environments. Use this only when you intentionally run a tightly curated subset of tool capabilities.","绝对工具允许列表，会替代配置档派生的默认值，适用于严格环境。仅在你明确要运行一组严格筛选的工具能力时使用。"],
["Tool Allowlist Additions","工具允许列表补充项"],
["Extra tool allowlist entries merged on top of the selected tool profile and default policy. Keep this list small and explicit so audits can quickly identify intentional policy exceptions.","在所选工具配置档和默认策略之上追加合并的额外工具允许项。建议该列表保持精简且明确，便于审计时快速识别有意设置的策略例外。"],
["Tool Policy by Provider","按提供方设置的工具策略"],
["Per-provider tool allow/deny overrides keyed by channel/provider ID to tailor capabilities by surface. Use this when one provider needs stricter controls than global tool policy.","按频道/提供方 ID 设置的工具允许/拒绝覆盖，用于针对不同接入面定制能力。适用于某个提供方需要比全局工具策略更严格控制时。"],
["Forward Exec Approvals","转发执行审批"],
["Top-level binding rules for routing and persistent ACP conversation ownership. Use type=route for normal routing and type=acp for persistent ACP harness bindings.","用于路由和持久 ACP 会话归属的顶层绑定规则。使用 type=route 进行普通路由，使用 type=acp 进行持久 ACP harness 绑定。"],
["Command Elevated Access Rules","命令提权访问规则"],
["Defines elevated command allow rules by channel and sender for owner-level command surfaces. Use narrow provider-specific identities so privileged commands are not exposed to broad chat audiences.","按频道和发送者定义提权命令的允许规则，用于 owner 级命令入口。建议使用收窄的提供方专属身份，避免将特权命令暴露给过宽的聊天受众。"],
["Allow Bash Chat Command","允许 Bash 聊天命令"],
["Allow bash chat command (`!`; `/bash` alias) to run host shell commands (default: false; requires tools.elevated).","允许通过 bash 聊天命令（`!`；`/bash` 别名）运行主机 shell 命令（默认：false；需要 tools.elevated）。"],
["Bash Foreground Window (ms)","Bash 前台窗口（毫秒）"],
["How long bash waits before backgrounding (default: 2000; 0 backgrounds immediately).","bash 在转入后台前等待的时间（默认：2000；设为 0 会立即后台化）。"],
["Allow /config","允许 /config"],
["Allow /config chat command to read/write config on disk (default: false).","允许 /config 聊天命令读取/写入磁盘上的配置（默认：false）。"],
["Allow /debug","允许 /debug"],
["Allow /debug chat command for runtime-only overrides (default: false).","允许 /debug 聊天命令进行仅运行时的覆盖（默认：false）。"],
["Native Commands","原生命令"],
["Registers native slash/menu commands with channels that support command registration (Discord, Slack, Telegram). Keep enabled for discoverability unless you intentionally run text-only command workflows.","在支持命令注册的频道中注册原生斜杠菜单命令（Discord、Slack、Telegram）。除非你明确只运行纯文本命令工作流，否则建议保持启用以提高可发现性。"],
["Native Skill Commands","原生技能命令"],
["Registers native skill commands so users can invoke skills directly from provider command menus where supported. Keep aligned with your skill policy so exposed commands match what operators expect.","注册原生技能命令，使用户能在支持的提供方命令菜单中直接调用技能。应与技能策略保持一致，确保暴露的命令符合操作者预期。"],
["Command Owners","命令所有者"],
["Explicit owner allowlist for owner-only tools/commands. Use channel-native IDs (optionally prefixed like \"whatsapp:+15551234567\"). '*' is ignored.","owner 专用工具/命令的显式允许列表。使用频道原生 ID（可选前缀如 “whatsapp:+15551234567”）。`*` 会被忽略。"],
["Owner ID Display","Owner ID 显示方式"],
["Controls how owner IDs are rendered in the system prompt. Allowed values: raw, hash. Default: raw.","控制 owner ID 在系统提示中的显示方式。允许值：raw、hash。默认：raw。"],
["Session Max Entries","会话最大条目数"],
["Caps total session entry count retained in the store to prevent unbounded growth over time. Use lower limits for constrained environments, or higher limits when longer history is required.","限制存储中保留的会话总条目数，防止随时间无限增长。资源受限环境建议较低值；若需要更长历史，可设置更高值。"],
["Session Prune After","会话清理期限"],
["Deprecated age-retention field kept for compatibility with legacy configs using day counts. Use session.maintenance.pruneAfter instead so duration syntax and behavior are consistent.","为兼容使用按天计数的旧配置而保留的过时保留期字段。建议改用 session.maintenance.pruneAfter，以保持时长语法和行为一致。"],
["Session Rotation Size","会话轮转大小"],
["Rotates the session store when file size exceeds a threshold such as `10mb` or `1gb`. Use this to bound single-file growth and keep backup/restore operations manageable.","当会话存储文件大小超过阈值（如 `10mb` 或 `1gb`）时执行轮转。可用于限制单文件增长，并让备份/恢复操作更易管理。"],
["Session Reset Trigger","会话重置触发器"],
["Session Scope","会话范围"],
["Sets base session grouping strategy: \"per-sender\" isolates by sender and \"global\" shares one session per channel context. Keep \"per-sender\" for safer multi-user behavior unless deliberate shared context is required.","设置基础会话分组策略：“per-sender” 按发送者隔离，“global” 则在每个频道上下文中共享一个会话。除非你明确需要共享上下文，否则建议使用 “per-sender” 以获得更安全的多用户行为。"],
["Session Maintenance Mode","会话维护模式"],
["Determines whether maintenance policies are only reported (\"warn\") or actively applied (\"enforce\"). Keep \"warn\" during rollout and switch to \"enforce\" after validating safe thresholds.","决定维护策略是仅报告（“warn”）还是实际执行（“enforce”）。上线初期建议保持“warn”，在验证阈值安全后再切换为“enforce”。"],
["Session Reset Policy","会话重置策略"],
["Selects reset strategy: \"daily\" resets at a configured hour and \"idle\" resets after inactivity windows. Keep one clear mode per policy to avoid surprising context turnover patterns.","选择重置策略：“daily” 会在设定小时重置，“idle” 会在空闲窗口后重置。建议每条策略只采用一种清晰模式，避免出现难以预期的上下文切换。"],
["Tools","工具"],
["Agent To Agent","代理到代理"],
["Bundled","内置包"],
["automation","自动化"],
["once","一次"],
["always","始终"],
["low","低"],
["medium","中"],
["high","高"],
["xhigh","极高"],
["adaptive","自适应"],
["builtin","内置"]
